# Requirements
Before the app can be authorized by **online** users, there are some pre-requisites for the app.
For custom apps:

1. The app has enabled **at least one** API scope user: seller, creator, and/or partner.
2. The app passes "enrollment review"

For public apps:

1. The app has enabled **at least one** API scope user: seller, creator, and/or partner.
2. The app passes "enrollment review"
3. The app passes "USDS/OPIS review" (only for US target market)
4. The app passes "Listing Review"
5. The app passes "App review"
6. The app passes "Beta Testing"(only for connector apps)

# Enable API Scope

Before developing an app, the developer should enable or apply for the necessary API scope depending on the app's business type.

# Obtain an authorization link
Generate an authorization link by clicking **Copy authorization link** in the **Authorization** section of your app:
<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">üìå </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"><strong>Note</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">: If the app is in the development stage, the </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"><strong>Copy authorization link</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"> button will be invisible. Please visit our </span>[seller authorization](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/seller-authorization-guide)<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">, </span>[creator authorization](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/creator-authorization-guide)<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">, or </span>[partner authorization](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/partner-authorization-guide)<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"> guides for more information.</span>
![Image](https://p16-arcosite-va.ibyteimg.com/tos-maliva-i-10qhjjqwgv-us/692b32d0629e4ef588013b41c17d8c13~tplv-10qhjjqwgv-image.image)
<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">üìå </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"><strong>Note</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">: Depending on which market you are in, the authorization link will be slightly different.</span>
<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"><strong>US</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">: https://services.tiktokshops.us/open/authorize?service_id=7369437808455026474</span>

* <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)"><strong>ROW (rest of the world)</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 235)">: https://services.tiktokshop.com/open/authorize?service_id=7431458374265161478</span>


A `state` parameter should be added to your authorization link for extra security. Please see the [OpenID Connect](https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/oauth2/openid-connect#createxsrftoken) documentation for an example of how to create and confirm a `state`.
After the user visits the authorization link, they must accept or reject the authorization.
If the user accepts the authorization request, they will be redirected to the **Redirect URL**, which will additionally contain a temporary **code** as a parameter. This code will be used as the **auth_code** when obtaining an access token in the following step.
## Redirect URL and `auth_code` example:
```plaintext
{redirect_url}?code=FeBoANmHP3yqdoUI9fZOCw&state={state}
```


<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)">‚ùó </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)"><strong>Important</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)">: The auth_code expires in </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)"><strong>30 minutes</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)"> and can only be used </span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)"><strong>once</strong></span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 235)">.</span>

![Image](https://p16-arcosite-va.ibyteimg.com/tos-maliva-i-10qhjjqwgv-us/6c31e0d01a514a5b8d720162cb5a84c1~tplv-10qhjjqwgv-image.image)
If the user rejects the authorization request, they will still be redirected to the **Redirect URL**, but instead the `code` will be null: `code=null&error=auth_denied`.
# Get Access Token API
To request an `access_token` and `refresh_token`, make a `GET` request to the `auth.tiktok-shops.com/api/v2/token/get` endpoint, with the following parameters:
| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required?** | **Description** | **Sample** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| app_key | string | Yes | App key in Partner Center app page. | 123abc |
| app_secret | string | Yes | App secret in Partner Center app page. | 15abf8a4972afd1f275d5b19bfa9a17e0d142aa7 |
| auth_code | string | Yes | Authorization code obtained using the authorization link. | TTP_FeBoANmHP3yqdoUI9fZOCw |
| grant_type | string | Yes | Grant token type. Only `authorized_code` is accepted as a value. | authorized_code |

Your request should resemble the following:
```plaintext
https://auth.tiktok-shops.com/api/v2/token/get?app_key=123abcd
&app_secret=15abf8a4972afd1f275d5b19bfa9a17e0d142aa7
&auth_code=TTP_FeBoANmHP3yqdoUI9fZOCw
&grant_type=authorized_code
```

If all the parameters entered in the `GET` request are valid, the response will contain the following parameters:
| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Description** | **Sample** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| code | int | A machine-readable response code that represents the request result. `0` indicates success. For more information about failure codes, refer to [Common error codes](common-errors). | 0 |
| message | string | A human-readable message that describes the success or failure of the API request. | success |
| request_id | string | ID to track the API request. | 20220808094623010 <br> 24509910319695C45 |
| data | object | The response data payload. |  |
| ‚îî access_token | string | User access token needed to make calls to TikTok Shop Open API endpoints. Pass this value in the `x-tts-access-token` header of an API request to authorize the request. | TTP_RLM6CIADWF <br> 606TZGFO5XGA |
| ‚îî access_token_expire_in | Unix timestamp | Expiration timestamp for access token, with default expiration time set to **seven days**. The unix timestamp represents the date and time the access token will expire. | 1630401330 |
| ‚îî refresh_token | string | A token to refresh the access token. | TTP_C2XWDN63ON- <br> FOHJSMR0WSG |
| ‚îî refresh_token_expire_in | Unix timestamp | Expiration timestamp for refresh token. The unix timestamp represents the date and time the refresh token will expire. | 1630401510 |
| ‚îî open_id | string | An ID used to identify the user who has authorized the retrieval of their data in API calls. | ephr6QAAAADhos3OBM <br> ztFEwRCWQGzDmfXm_ <br> 7O2OTJyaYKA15pIaiEg |
| ‚îî seller_name | string | The name of the seller you are authorizing for your app. | Test Name |
| ‚îî seller_base_region | string | The region where the seller is based. | US |
| ‚îî user_type | int | Type of user, with possible values: <br>  <br> * 0: Seller <br> * 1: Creator <br> * 3: Partner | 1 |
| ‚îî granted_scopes | []string | The authorized API scopes for the app. <br> This field will return the **Scope Key** value of the authorized API scopes. <br>  <br> ![Image](https://p16-arcosite-va.ibyteimg.com/tos-maliva-i-10qhjjqwgv-us/a28585cf3cec42c2846c13f2cfaec033~tplv-10qhjjqwgv-image.image) | ["seller.affiliate_collaboration.read", <br> "seller.affiliate_collaboration.write"] |

# Get Refresh Token API
To refresh your `access_token`, make a `GET` request to the `auth.tiktok-shops.com/api/v2/token/refresh` endpoint, with the following parameters:
| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required?** | **Description** | **Sample** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| app_key | string | Yes | App key in the TikTok Shop Partner Center app page. | 65t60877bfejb |
| app_secret | string | Yes | App secret in the Tiktok Shop Partner Center app page. | 15abf8a4972afd1f275d5b19bfa9a17e0d142aa7 |
| refresh_token | string | Yes | A refresh token obtained in the response parameters of the Get Access Token API. | TTP_C2XWDN63ON-FOHJSMR0WSG |
| grant_type | string | Yes | Grant token type. Only `refresh_token` is accepted. | refresh_token |

Your request should resemble the following:
```plaintext
https://auth.tiktok-shops.com/api/v2/token/refresh?app_key=65t6a8e8bfejb
&app_secret=f4c770e4b45aa62e
&refresh_token=TTP_EB9rlwAAAADXbnMESTWAZSxIcC-XUA5AyeEOdmGBKY2FiKFYKqON6jco
&grant_type=refresh_token
```

If all the parameters entered in the `GET` request are valid, the response will contain the following parameters:
